--- !u!114 &8138723596770070095
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 4363965007950127340}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: a40ba246606b23944b5c0dc49e9a6241, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::FishCodex
  FishEntries:
  - Name: Reef Shark
    Description: 'Reef Sharks are slender, agile predators that inhabit tropical
      and subtropical coral reefs. They have streamlined bodies, rounded snouts,
      and distinct fin markings. They are vital to maintaining marine ecosystem health
      by keeping smaller predators in check, balancing the food chain.



      Average
      size of 3 to 6 feet in length.



      The earliest scientific description
      of Reef sharks was back in 1824.

'
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Barracuda
    Description: 'Barracudas are sleek, aggressive predatory fish belonging to the
      family Sphyraenidae, renowned for their fearsome appearance, explosive speed,
      and dagger-like teeth. Found globally in warm, tropical, and subtropical waters,
      they are highly efficient ambush hunters that patrol coral reefs, mangroves,
      and seagrass beds.


      Average size of 2 to 3 feet in length.



      The
      earliest scientific description of the Barracuda was back in 1771.

'
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Manta Ray
    Description: 'Manta rays are majestic, harmless giants of the ocean known for
      their massive, diamond-shaped bodies, horn-like facial fins, and graceful,
      bird-like swimming motions. Unlike stingrays, they possess no stinging venomous
      spine and are completely gentle filter feeders.


      Average size of 10
      to 11 feet in length.


      The earliest scientific description of the Manta
      Ray was back in 1792.'
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Jellyfish
    Description: "Jellyfish are ancient, free-swimming marine invertebrates belonging
      to the phylum Cnidaria, defined by their gelatinous, umbrella-shaped bells
      and trailing, stinging tentacles. They have drifted in the world's oceans for
      over 500 million years, making them older than dinosaurs, and they completely
      lack brains, hearts, bones, or blood. \r\n\nAverage size of 2 to 6 feet in
      length.\r\n\nThe earliest scientific description of the Jellyfish was back
      in 1758.\r\n"
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Clownfish
    Description: "Clownfish (also called anemonefish) are small, brightly colored
      marine fish belonging to the subfamily Amphiprioninae. Found in the warm waters
      of the Indian and Pacific Oceans, they are famous for their strict symbiotic
      relationship with venomous sea anemones, which protect them from predators.
      \r\n\nAverage size of 0.25 to 0.3 foot in length.\r\n\nThe earliest scientific
      description of the Clownfish was back in 1830.\r\n"
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Rabbitfish
    Description: 'Rabbitfish (belonging to the family Siganidae) are small to medium-sized,
      herbivorous marine fish found throughout shallow coastal waters, coral reefs,
      and seagrass beds in the Indo-Pacific and eastern Mediterranean. They are named
      for their unique, rabbit-like snouts and grazing habits.


      Average size
      of 0.65 to 1 foot in length.


      The earliest scientific description of
      the Rabbitfish was back in 1775.

'
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Sardine
    Description: "Sardines (also known as pilchards) are small, nutrient-rich schooling
      fish belonging to the herring family Clupeidae. Found globally in massive coastal
      upwelling zones, they are essential filter feeders that serve as the fundamental
      foundation of the marine food web. \r\n\nAverage size of 0.5 to 0.65 foot in
      length.\r\n\nThe earliest scientific description of the Sardine was back in
      1758.\r\n"
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Vampire Squid
    Description: "Vampire Squids (Vampyroteuthis infernalis, which translates to
      \"vampire squid from hell\") are unique, ancient cephalopods that inhabit the
      deep, pitch-black waters of the ocean's twilight zone. Despite their name,
      they are not true squids or octopuses, but rather the lone surviving members
      of their own distinct evolutionary order (Vampyromorphida). \r\n\nAverage size
      of 0.8 to 1 foot in length.\r\n\nThe earliest scientific description of the
      Vampire Squid was back in 1903.\r\n"
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Pelican Eel
    Description: "Pelican eels (also known as gulper eels or Eurypharynx pelecanoides)
      are extraordinary, bizarre deep-sea fish inhabiting the ocean's twilight zone.
      They are famous for their oversized, loosely hinged jaws and highly distensible
      throats, which can inflate like a massive balloon to scoop up prey. \r\n\nAverage
      size of 2 to 2.5 feet in length.\r\n\nThe earliest scientific description of
      the Pelican Eel was back in 1882\r\n"
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Dragonfish
    Description: "Deep-sea dragonfish (belonging to the family Stomiidae) are terrifyingly
      fierce, ambush predators that inhabit the twilight zone of the global ocean.
      Despite looking like an alien nightmare with oversized, translucent fangs,
      they are surprisingly small, highly specialized survivors of the extreme deep.
      \r\n\nAverage size of 0.4 to 0.8 foot in length\r\n\nThe earliest scientific
      description of the Dragonfish was back in 1833.\r\n"
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Hatchetfish
    Description: 'Marine hatchetfish (belonging to the family Sternoptychidae) are
      tiny, bizarre deep-sea fish that live in the ocean''s twilight zone. They get
      their name from their extremely thin, razor-like bodies that perfectly resemble
      the silver blade of a handaxe.


      Average size of 0.1 to 0.25 foot in
      length.


      The earliest scientific description of the Hatchetfish was
      back in 1856.

'
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Spider Shark
    Description: "Spider sharks are a bizarre and puzzling scientific anomaly of
      a deep-sea fish, they possess the body of a shark but with multiple eyes that
      correlate to a spider. They are the primary predator of the twilight zone as
      it is very aggressive. They\u2019re the first ever anomaly discovered in the
      New Mariana Trench.\r\n\nAverage size of 3 to 6 feet in length.\r\n\nThe earliest
      scientific description of the Spider Shark was after the Anomaly Event of 2026.\r\n"
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Anglerfish
    Description: "Anglerfish (belonging to the order Lophiiformes) are predatory
      fish famously known for their terrifying appearance and highly specialized
      hunting methods. Found worldwide, they range from shallow reefs to the pitch-black
      Midnight Zone of the deep sea, defined by a modified dorsal fin spine that
      functions like a fishing rod to lure prey. \r\n\nAverage size of 0.3 to 0.7
      foot in length.\r\n\nThe earliest scientific description of the Anglerfish
      was back in 1758.\r\n"
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Goblin Shark
    Description: "Goblin sharks are rare, bottom-dwelling deep-sea sharks easily
      recognized by their long, trowel-like snouts and highly extendable pink jaws.
      They inhabit the Midnight Zone, usually cruising near the seafloor. \r\n\nAverage
      size of 10 to 13 feet in length.\r\n\nThe earliest scientific description of
      the Goblin Shark was back in 1898.\r\n"
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Giant Squid
    Description: "The Giant Squid is an enormous deep-sea cephalopod that patrols
      the Midnight Zone. They are aggressive hunters that actively chase down deep-sea
      fish and other squid species. \r\n\nAverage size of 33 to 43 feet in length.\r\n\nThe
      earliest scientific description of the Giant Squid was back in 1857.\r\n"
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Fincrab
    Description: 'The Fincrab is an abomination that resembles the body of a Goblin
      Shark mixed with the components and foundations of a Crab with the claws and
      its extended legs that helps with its mobility. This anomaly is discovered
      to be roaming the Midnight Zone.


      Average size of 8 to 12 feet in length.


      The
      earliest scientific description of the Fincrab was after the Anomaly Event
      of 2026

'
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Frilled Shark
    Description: "Frilled sharks are primitive, eel-like sharks that live on the
      outer continental shelves and upper slopes. They roam the deep seas of the
      Midnight Zone. \r\n\nAverage size of 4.5 to 5.5 feet in length.\r\n\nThe earliest
      scientific description of the Frilled Shark was back in 1884.\r\n"
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Tripod Fish
    Description: 'The Tripod Fish is a bizarre, sedentary deep-sea creature that
      lives in the crushing darkness of the Abyss Zone. They are famous for standing
      completely still on the ocean floor like a camera tripod.


      Average size
      of 0.8 to 1 foot in length.


      The earliest scientific description of
      the Tripod Fish was back in 1887.

'
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Skeletal Fish
    Description: 'The Skeletal Fish is an anomaly that is known for its unusual skeletal-like
      body, venturing the Abyss Zone, its skeletal body is a colony of microorganisms
      that work together to make the creature function for them to look bigger as
      to survive and have a chance in the food chain, altogether resembling a Skeletal
      figure. It is the first recorded anomaly that is very passive unlike the others.


      Average
      size of 1 to 2.3 feet in length.


      The earliest scientific description
      of the Skeletal Fish was after the Anomaly Event of 2026.

'
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Grisly Shark
    Description: 'The Grisly Shark is an anomaly that is known for its horrific features
      that feature different body parts throughout. It seems to attempt to mimic
      the rest of the creatures in the Abyss Zone as a way to adapt and intimidate.
      It roams the deep Abyss Zone.


      Average size of 11 to 14 feet in length.


      The
      earliest scientific description of the Grisly Shark was after the Anomaly Event
      of 2026.

'
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: 'EMO '
    Description: "The Enlarged Mutated Isopod is an armored, deep-sea crustacean
      that acts as a prime example of deep-sea gigantism mixed with the New Mariana
      Trench\u2019s anomaly event. Closely related to the tiny woodlice or \"pillbugs\"
      found in backyards, these massive scavengers crawl along the mud of the Abyss
      Zone. Due to the recent event, their size has grown tremendously and have been
      mutated to where their mobility is now also enhanced.\t\r\n\nAverage size of
      3 to 5 feet in length.\r\n\nThe earliest scientific description of the SEnlarged
      Mutated Isopod was after the Anomaly Event of 2026.\r\n"
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Monster Eel
    Description: 'The Monster Eel is the apex predator of the Abyss Zone. Known for
      its tremendously long snake-like scaleless body, it resembles the identity
      of the Conger Eel. The anomaly is known to be very vicious to other creatures
      in the zone it shares as its appetite is known to be very short and fast due
      to the pressure mixed with its size.


      Average size of 20 to 25 feet
      in length.


      The earliest scientific description of the Monster Eel was
      after the Anomaly Event of 2026.

'
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Mariana Snailfish
    Description: 'The Mariana snailfish (Pseudoliparis swirei) is a small, ghost-like
      deep-sea fish famous for being the deepest dwelling fish ever captured on the
      seafloor before the anomaly event. Thriving in the Hadal zone, they are the
      undisputed apex predators of their extreme, crushing environment before the
      anomaly event.


      Average size of 0.5 to 0.8 foot in length.


      The
      earliest scientific description of the Mariana Snailfish was back in 2017.

'
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Large Blood Snapper
    Description: 'The Large Blood Snapper is a large anomaly recorded to be the very
      first blood based anomaly that lives deep within the Hadal Zone, it is known
      for its very bloody colored body that migrated from the Blood Zone after the
      anomaly event to adapt to a new environment. It''s known for its snapping jaw
      that immediately engulfs another creature in less than a second.


      Average
      size of 24 to 28 feet in length.


      The earliest scientific description
      of the Large Blood Snapper was after the Anomaly Event of 2026.



'
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Nightwing
    Description: "The Nightwing is a large anomaly known for its night-like body
      filled with various small lights that resemble stars in a midnight sky that
      stands out in the Abyss Zone. It also has an outstanding body feature resembling
      wings as its side fins. \r\n\nAverage size of 30 to 35 feet in length.\r\n\nThe
      earliest scientific description of the Nightwing was after the Anomaly Event
      of 2026.\r\n"
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Ancient Piranha
    Description: 'The Ancient Piranhas are a previously-thought extinct species that
      is now discovered to be still around as it was residing in the Blood Zone when
      it was thought to be extinct. In comparison with the usual piranhas, it is
      more grisly and bigger as it adapted towards the environment of the Blood Zone
      but is now back and residing in the Hadal Zone.


      Average size of 5
      to 6 feet in length.


      The earliest scientific description of the Ancient
      Piranha was back in 2009.

'
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Blood Burden
    Description: 'Description for this anomaly remains unknown.


      The average
      size of the anomaly is currently unknown.


      There is no scientific description
      of this anomaly.

'
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Blood Torment
    Description: 'Description for this anomaly remains unknown.


      The average
      size of the anomaly is currently unknown.


      There is no scientific description
      of this anomaly.

'
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: Grotesque Kingfish
    Description: 'Description for this anomaly remains unknown.


      The average
      size of the anomaly is currently unknown.


      There is no scientific description
      of this anomaly.

'
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
  - Name: ???
    Description: "Creature of its only remaining species that has survived the entirety
      of Earth\u2019s history. \r\n\nThe average size of the anomaly is currently
      unknown.\r\n\nThere is no scientific description of this anomaly.\r\n"
    FishImage: {fileID: 0}
    IsUnlocked: 0
